<br>
While I agree it was not originally intended, I think VI's goals changed when DAoC was launched. I think KEI being available for low levels is now intentional.<br>
<br>
My evidence is only indirect - the lack of a nerf in 2 years and the introduction of MGB with the same problem. While I perfectly accept that they can take an inordinate period of time to fix old bugs I would have at least expected them to design MGB with this bug in mind.<br>
<br>
I am never suprised when they fix things that are overly powerful though as KEI on a lvl 1 obviously is; I was not really suprised when they fixed horses in the old models (though I objected to the method they used) and I was not suprised when they stopped affliction haste working on charm/slow/malo etc (both after a long period).<br>
<br>
I would also not be suprised if they stopped kei on low levels though I think they would be very brave .. they'd lose many more customers than they'd gain and you'd have all the usual complaints about SoE 'only wanting people to play longer so they get more money' and 'the ubers have taken advantage and now the casuals get hurt' yadda yadda. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=niinjaturtle>niinjaturtle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/1/03 6:34:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25564.topic&index=102>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.wowexpress.com/dreadscale/kan2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Define &quot;exploit&quot;</span><hr size=1> not exploit<br>
