<br>
I am of two thoughts on this.  In many ways it is too powerful, but only in theory.  A solo caster, still has the down time like a melee as even with KEI you get hit.  So the down time at the lowest levels then becomes equal to melee is based on HP regen.<br>
<br>
Mid-level (abt 15 to 40 ish) it changes the dynamics of the game just a bit.<br>
<br>
Now when compared to a twink melee with an insane AC, and yes 2k HPs without Aego ( it is not that hard to do)  KEI on the casters then brings some balance back to the game.  <br>
<br>
With unlimited mana from KEI at these levels means you really do not learn mana management, but lets be honest here, mana management is not a big deal anymore.  <br>
<br>
THe more important thing people learn is aggro management, since essentially you can nuke/ heal non stop with the mana regen unless you draw aggro.  <br>
<br>
I for one use KEI on my alt casters since they cannot be twinked real easy at lower levels.  My melee alt, is a Rallos Zek worshipping ogre,  by level 25 he had over 2K HPs with his gear.  Hell at lvl 10 he had well over 1k HPs.  <br>
<br>
TO ME ALL KEI IS ANOTHER FORM OF TWINKING A CHARACTER. <br>
<br>
For this issue I am not going to say or even claim to know what VI and now Sony ever intended with the level restriction on buffs, being able to cast group buffs on lower level players.  Once they come out and say it then fine I will abide by whatever they state.  Until such time I will continue to use KEI on my baby casters.<br>
<br>
Sage Arcanist Silverleaf<br>
Semi-retired Tunare<br>
<br>
Irrdaan<br>
lvl 14 wizard<br>
