<br>
For instance how is just sitting in the Nexus when an MGB KEI goes off an exploit?  I guess you could stand and run screaming towards the south tunnel so as not to be in violation.  What if you are akf?  <br>
<br>
Another example.  I was afk with my level 6 wizard in PoK and I came back to find someone had cast Temperence on me (800 hp plus ? ac buff).  I was one happy wizard!  I used it to hunt down yellows solo in Shadeweaver's Thicket - was I exploiting or was the guy who cast it exploiting?  I can guarantee that having 800-odd hps at level 6 is unnatural.<br>
<br>
I suppose in both instances the 'right' thing to do would have been to avert my eyes and click that offending buff off so you would not be in violation.  But honestly how many would click off KEI or Aego or something like that voluntarily?  I bet only a small minority could do that when push comes to shove.  And frankly they shouldn't have to - its Sony's responsability to make sure such unbalancing things can't happen imho. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whizbangdustyboots>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Arcanist<BR>Gnomus Originalus</span><br>  Posts: 12279<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/1/03 7:44:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25564.topic&index=114>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz-side-02.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well...</span><hr size=1> The vast majority of people under 45 seek out an enchanter and pay them money to buff them and have to drop their groups to do so.<br>
